    "summary": "The last years I have been working on a large expansion project. One of 4 expansion projects I have worked on. I was Project Engineer for the disciplines Mechanical, HVAC and partly Piping (not in execution phase) from the study phase, FEED and execution phase of the project. I have been the lead of the team preparing the purchase of 60 requisitions of machines and equipment, engineering the HVAC systems and piping systems. Responsible for the requisitions/specifications, selecting vendors, technical evaluation of the bids, providing technical support for the vendors (e.g. in case of deviations/problems) and ensuring overall quality control. I am used to work with together with big engineering companies like Worley/Fluor and manufactures all over Europe.\n\nI need complex technical challenges and problems for my satisfaction. New technologies and new knowledge areas I find very attractive. Finding a solution beyond the obvious. Within Teijin Aramid I have had many projects that meet this and that I enjoy.\n\nWorking with people and achieve the best possible added value to the company and the people is what satisfies me also. For me working together with people means: accepting them as they are and challenge them to perform at their maximum to reach the goals of the project. The differences between people are needed to challenge all members in the project team. I see it as my responsibility to challenge every team member and make the whole team perform at its best and deliver the best possible result for the company.\n\nKey words (random order):\nPeople\nProject Management\nMechanical engineering\nMachinery, CE\nManufactoring\nMechanical static equipment\nRotating equipment\nPiping\nHVAC systems",
