            "description": "As a Project Engineer in an extension project I have full responsibility for my disciplines, mechanical and HVAC. It is my responsibility to meet the goals of the project together with the engineering companies and contractors and other project team members of Teijin Aramid (in short: purchasing department, production, maintenance, process, civil, electrical and instrumentation engineers). In short: I act as a controlling gateway between Teijin Aramid and the lead engineers of the engineering contractor(s) to make sure that all necessary internal knowledge is also available for and applied by the EC project team.\nAs an mechanical Project Engineer I have to work very close with all disciplines in order to achieve the highest level of quality of the project result. This begins with contribution to (3D) plant layout reviews, HAZOP, SIL and RI&E sessions. Generating the Technical Requisitions for the various equipment and facilities, vendor selections, bid evaluations, inspection, acceptance tests at factory or at site also require a lot of cooperation with all disciplines. Finally the project ends with support for the commissioning and startup team and handling of spare parts, operating and maintenance instructions.\n",
